    "We sequenced the samples for 72 h using a single R9.4/FLO-MIN106 flow cell (Oxford Nanopore Technologies).",
    "For B. fragilis n-216, DNA fragmentation was performed on 10 µg DNA (in 250 µl) using ten passes through a 22 G needle.",
    "A total Analysis https://doi.org/10.1038/s41564-024-01610-3 of input 0.32-0.44 µg genomic DNA (in 8.5 µl) plus 1.5 µl fragmentation was used as input.",
    "The samples were sequenced for 72 h using a single R9.4/FLO-MIN106 flow cell.",
    "We used Guppy (v4.0.15) for all post-run base calling, sample de-multiplexing and the conversion of raw FAST5 files to FASTQ files."
